From: Kamil Bienkiewicz <perceivalpercy@gmail.com>
Date: Sat, 23 May 2026 10:50:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] net: ethernet: qcom: ppe: edma: advance cons_idx on null-skb
 abort

Patch 0554 added NULL-skb guards to `edma_rx_reap` so the kernel
doesn't deref NULL when the IPQ5332 EDMA hands us a phantom or
duplicate descriptor. But the pre-loop guard `return 0` doesn't
advance cons_idx, so the next NAPI tick sees the same descriptor,
hits the same NULL, and aborts again. With HW continuously signaling
RX available, this becomes a NAPI livelock — millions of callbacks
per second, ratelimit-suppressed prints still saturate the console,
and the rdinit shell becomes unresponsive.

Fix: when the pre-loop guard fires, also write `cons_idx = (cons_idx
+ 1) & MASK` and commit it to HW, so the descriptor is consumed and
NAPI moves on. Same for the inner-loop scatter path. The linear
inner-loop path already `break`s out of the loop which falls through
to the existing tail that commits cons_idx, so it's already correct.

Also demote the pr_warn_ratelimited to pr_debug_ratelimited — once
the cons_idx advances, the print isn't load-bearing, and even
ratelimited it dominated the console under heavy bad-descriptor flow.

Signed-off-by: Kamil Bienkiewicz <perceivalpercy@gmail.com>
---
--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/qualcomm/ppe/edma_rx.c
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/qualcomm/ppe/edma_rx.c
@@ -488,8 +488,16 @@ static int edma_rx_reap(struct edma_rxdesc_ring *rxdesc_ring, int budget)
 		next_skb = rxdesc_ring->rxfill->skbs[idx];
 		rxdesc_ring->rxfill->skbs[idx] = NULL;
 		if (unlikely(!next_skb)) {
-			pr_warn_ratelimited("edma_rx_reap: NULL skb at idx %u (stale/dup desc); aborting batch\n",
-					    idx);
+			/* Advance past the bad descriptor so HW doesn't
+			 * keep re-signaling RX on the same slot.
+			 */
+			pr_debug_ratelimited("edma_rx_reap: NULL skb at idx %u; skipping\n",
+					     idx);
+			cons_idx = (cons_idx + 1) & EDMA_RX_RING_SIZE_MASK;
+			rxdesc_ring->cons_idx = cons_idx;
+			reg = EDMA_BASE_OFFSET +
+			      EDMA_REG_RXDESC_CONS_IDX(rxdesc_ring->ring_id);
+			regmap_write(regmap, reg, cons_idx);
 			return 0;
 		}
 	}
@@ -544,8 +552,8 @@ static int edma_rx_reap(struct edma_rxdesc_ring *rxdesc_ring, int budget)
 				next_skb = rxdesc_ring->rxfill->skbs[idx];
 				rxdesc_ring->rxfill->skbs[idx] = NULL;
 				if (unlikely(!next_skb)) {
-					pr_warn_ratelimited("edma_rx_reap: NULL skb (linear next) at idx %u\n",
-							    idx);
+					pr_debug_ratelimited("edma_rx_reap: NULL skb (linear next) at idx %u\n",
+							     idx);
 					dev_kfree_skb_any(skb);
 					break;
 				}
@@ -564,8 +572,8 @@ static int edma_rx_reap(struct edma_rxdesc_ring *rxdesc_ring, int budget)
 			next_skb = rxdesc_ring->rxfill->skbs[idx];
 			rxdesc_ring->rxfill->skbs[idx] = NULL;
 			if (unlikely(!next_skb)) {
-				pr_warn_ratelimited("edma_rx_reap: NULL skb (scatter next) at idx %u\n",
-						    idx);
+				pr_debug_ratelimited("edma_rx_reap: NULL skb (scatter next) at idx %u\n",
+						     idx);
 				break;
 			}
 		}
